"539","control over financial reporting. Accordingly, we express no such opinion.&#160; </font></p>"
"540","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;><font face=EYInterstate Light lang=EN-US style=font-size:9.0pt;>&nbsp;</font></p>"
"541","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;><font face=EYInterstate Light lang=EN-US style=font-size:9.0pt;>The management of the Company is responsible"
"542","for establishing and maintaining effective internal control over financial reporting."
"543","In fulfilling this responsibility, estimates and judgments by management are"
"544","required to assess the expected benefits and related costs of controls. A"
"545","company&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting is a process designed to"
"546","provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of financial reporting"
"547","and the preparation of financial statements for external purposes in accordance"
"548","with generally accepted accounting principles. A company&#8217;s internal control"
"549","over financial reporting includes those policies and procedures that (1)"
"550","pertain to the maintenance of records that, in reasonable detail, accurately"
"551","and fairly reflect the transactions and dispositions of the assets of the"
"552","company; (2) provide reasonable assurance that transactions are recorded as"
"553","necessary to permit preparation of financial statements in accordance with"
"554","generally accepted accounting principles, and that receipts and expenditures of"
"555","the company are being made only in accordance with authorizations of management"
"556","and directors of the company; and (3) provide reasonable assurance regarding"
"557","prevention or timely detection of unauthorized acquisition, use or disposition"
"558","of a company&#8217;s assets that could have a material effect on the financial"
"559","statements.</font></p>"
"560","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;><font face=EYInterstate Light lang=EN-US style=font-size:9.0pt;>&nbsp;</font></p>"
"561","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;><font face=EYInterstate Light lang=EN-US style=font-size:9.0pt;>Because of its inherent limitations, internal"
"562","control over financial reporting may not prevent or detect misstatements. Also,"
"563","projections of any evaluation of effectiveness to future periods are subject to"
"564","the risk that controls may become inadequate because of changes in conditions,"
"565","or that the degree of compliance with the policies or procedures may"
"566","deteriorate.</font></p>"
"567","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;><font face=EYInterstate Light lang=EN-US style=font-size:9.0pt;>&nbsp;</font></p>"
"568","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;><font face=EYInterstate Light lang=EN-US style=font-size:9.0pt;>A deficiency in internal control over"
"569","financial reporting exists when the design or operation of a control does not"
"570","allow management or employees, in the normal course of performing their"
"571","assigned functions, to prevent or detect misstatements on a timely basis. A"
"572","material weakness is a deficiency, or a combination of deficiencies, in"
"573","internal control over financial reporting, such that there is a reasonable"
"574","possibility that a material misstatement of the company&#8217;s annual or interim"
"575","financial statements will not be prevented or detected on a timely basis. </font></p>"
"576","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;><font face=EYInterstate Light lang=EN-US style=font-size:9.0pt;>&nbsp;</font></p>"
"577","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;><font face=EYInterstate Light lang=EN-US style=font-size:9.0pt;>Our consideration of the Company&#8217;s internal"
"578","control over financial reporting was for the limited purpose described in the"
"579","first paragraph and would not necessarily disclose all deficiencies in internal"
"580","control that might be material weaknesses under standards established by the"
"581","Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States). However, we noted no"
"582","deficiencies in the Company&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting and its"
"583","operation, including controls over safeguarding securities, that we consider to"
"584","be a material weakness as defined above as of May 31, 2011.</font></p>"
"585","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;><font face=EYInterstate Light lang=EN-US style=font-size:9.0pt;>&nbsp;</font></p>"
"586","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;><font face=EYInterstate Light lang=EN-US style=font-size:9.0pt;>This report is intended solely for the"
"587","information and use of management and the Board of Directors of Dreyfus Intermediate"
"588","Municipal Bond Fund, Inc. and the Securities and Exchange Commission and is not"
"589","intended to be and should not be used by anyone other than these specified"
"590","parties.</font></p>"
